Tools and technologies used in my CRUD API project:

Backend
1. Node.js: A JavaScript runtime environment for building server-side applications.
2. Express.js: A popular Node.js framework for building web applications and APIs.

Database
1. MongoDB: A NoSQL database management system for storing and retrieving data.
2. Mongoose: An Object Data Modeling (ODM) library for MongoDB and Node.js.

API Testing
1. Postman: A popular tool for testing and debugging APIs.

Deployment
1. MongoDB Atlas: A cloud-based MongoDB database service for hosting and managing MongoDB databases.

Development Tools
1. JavaScript: The programming language used for building the backend application.
2. npm (Node Package Manager): A package manager for installing and managing dependencies in Node.js projects.

These are the tools & technologies used in my CRUD project
